"explanation": "The defendant, acting in a position of fiduciary trust as an accountant, committed a serious breach of duty by embezzling $25,000. However, the court acknowledges several mitigating factors: the defendant has no prior criminal record, the motivation was to resolve personal debt rather than fund a lavish lifestyle, and they have demonstrated remorse through partial restitution. A 12-month sentence is appropriate to serve as a deterrent and reflect the gravity of the breach of trust while acknowledging the low risk of recidivism and existing efforts to compensate the victim.",
"verdict": 12
}
